eam","name":"stdout","text":["\n","Summary of Concerning Data Sharing Practices (Flo, Clue, Ovia):\n","----------------------------------------------------------------------\n","\n","App: Flo (Total concerning sentences: 15)\n","  - Sentence: 'We will share your personal data with our service providers who support our Services as described in this Privacy Policy.'\n","    Confidence: 0.6503\n","  - Sentence: 'We will also not use information received through your use of the Apple HealthKit or Google Health Connect framework for advertising or similar services, or sell it to advertising platforms, data brokers, or information resellers.'\n","    Confidence: 0.9575\n","  - Sentence: 'Objection to the processing of your personal data You have the right to object to the processing of your personal data, for example, if we process it for direct marketing purposes.'\n","    Confidence: 0.6056\n","\n","App: Clue (Total concerning sentences: 4)\n","  - Sentence: 'By teaming up with our trusted research partners we can advance research, break harmful taboos and lay the groundwork for better healthcare.'\n","    Confidence: 0.3759\n","  - Sentence: 'Research partners: We team up with carefully selected research partners both in and outside of the European Union.'\n","    Confidence: 0.7056\n","  - Sentence: 'Whenever data is transferred to partners outside of the European Economic Area (EEA), we always apply the appropriate safeguards as outlined by the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) (see Section 4).'\n","    Confidence: 0.3396\n","\n","App: Ovia (Total concerning sentences: 34)\n","  - Sentence: 'Introduction and scope This Ovia Health by Labcorp Apps Privacy Policy (“Policy”) describes how Ovuline, Inc., doing business as Ovia Health by Labcorp (“Ovia”) collects, uses and shares personal data collected through the Ovia apps, health coaching, surveys, and related social media and marketing activities (the “Services”).'\n","    Confidence: 0.8165\n","  - Sentence: 'When We Share Personal Information, What Categories of Recipients Do We Share With?'\n","    Confidence: 0.6424\n","  - Sentence: 'Categories of Recipients Examples of Recipients We Share With Service Providers and Contractors Ovia’s data is processed and stored by service providers and contractors working on Ovia’s behalf, including our cloud services provider Amazon Web Services, Helpshift (support services platform), Salesforce.com (coaching platform), Alchemer (survey platform) and Zoom Video Communications (coaching communications).'\n","    Confidence: 0.9450\n","\n","Summary of Protective Data Sharing Practices (Flo, Clue, Ovia):\n","----------------------------------------------------------------------\n","\n","App: Flo (Total protective sentences: 5)\n","  - Sentence: 'You can contribute to the growth of the Flo community If you consent, we may use technical information about your device and other information about you (such as your device’s unique technical identifier, age group, subscription status, emails and the fact you launch the app) to reach you for promotional purposes.'\n","    Confidence: 0.5890\n","  - Sentence: 'Third-party services (including wearables): With your consent, you may also allow us to connect to third-party services, such as Apple HealthKit and Google Health Connect.'\n","    Confidence: 0.9552\n","  - Sentence: 'Promoting our Services With your consent, we may share some of your non-health personal data with AppsFlyer to promote the Services.'\n","    Confidence: 0.9618\n","\n","App: Clue (Total protective sentences: 4)\n","  - Sentence: 'Amazon Web Services: Clue uses Amazon Web Services EMEA SARL (“AWS”) as our hosting provider to store our data on secure servers.'\n","    Confidence: 0.9140\n","  - Sentence: 'Legal basis: The processing of your usage data for website analytics is based on the following consent according to Art 6 Sec.1 lit a) GDPR: By using our website you consent through an opt-in in the cookie banner that Clue may use cookies and third-party services, and collect your usage data under a unique identifier for the purposes of tracking, analysis, and improvement of our website, as well as advertising purposes such as showing you relevant Clue content.'\n","    Confidence: 0.8874\n","  - Sentence: 'HTTPS is the same technology used to create secure connections for your web browser and is indicated by a padlock icon in the URL bar of your browser.'\n","    Confidence: 0.5160\n","\n","App: Ovia (Total protective sentences: 3)\n","  - Sentence: 'Ovia+ Customers and their Business Associates and Health Benefit Providers If you are an Ovia+ user, we may share data with your health insurer, health plan, employer, or their business associates and benefits management providers, as described below under the heading “Ovia+ Data Sharing”, provided that we share information with your employer only for specific uses and only if you expressly consent.'\n","    Confidence: 0.8710\n","  - Sentence: 'This limited purchase data is only used by our support staff to request refunds for you when appropriate, and is not shared with any third party.'\n","    Confidence: 0.7701\n","  - Sentence: 'If you do not provide consent to us, we will not be able to personalize your ads or measure your use of our services.'\n","    Confidence: 0.7277\n","\n","\n","Key Observations for Flo, Clue, and Ovia's Data Sharing Practices:\n","----------------------------------------------------------------------\n","Ovia tends to have more explicitly concerning data sharing statements, often mentioning advertising IDs, networks, and compensation for data, indicating a higher risk profile for data monetization.\n","Clue's concerning statements often relate to sharing with third-party providers and advertising identifiers, but also includes notes about de-identified data sharing with partners like Oura.\n","Flo's concerning statements often point to sharing with marketing and promotional partners (e.g., AppsFlyer, Pinterest, Google Ads, Meta Audience) and explicitly addresses the use of health framework data for advertising (though stating they *will not* for specific frameworks, this flags the concern).\n","Across all three, there's a mix of general 'service provider' language that can sometimes mask underlying data sharing activities. The protective language, where present, typically focuses on user consent, control, and commitments not to sell data.\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":354},"id":"1598ef81","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1763066154012,"user_tz":360,"elapsed":58,"user":{"displayName":"Alexis Prieto","userId":"17070250717485939340"}},"outputId":"bf4fc9f6-3a57-455c-e810-972b6e9e2039"},"source":["import pandas as pd\n","\n","# Assuming concerning_sharing_df is already available from previous steps\n","# If not, recreate it:\n","# results_df = pd.read_csv('bert_full_predictions_updated.csv')\n","# sharing_sentences_df = results_df[results_df['predicted_label'] == 'Data Sharing/Third Parties'].copy()\n","# protective_keywords = ['not shared', 'consent', 'opt-out', 'private', 'secure', 'encrypt', 'control over', 'only with', 'do not sell', 'do not rent', 'limited purpose']\n","# concerning_keywords = ['share with', 'third parties for advertising', 'sell', 'partners', 'marketing', 'affiliates', 'disclosure to', 'for business purposes', 'transfer data', 'monetary gain', 'service providers']\n","# for index, row in sharing_sentences_df.iterrows():\n","#     sentence = str(row['sentence']).lower()\n","#     is_protective = any(re.search(r'\\\\b' + keyword + r'\\\\b', sentence) for keyword in protective_keywords)\n","#     is_concerning = any(re.search(r'\\\\b' + keyword + r'\\\\b', sentence) for keyword in concerning_keywords)\n","#     if is_protective and not is_concerning: sharing_sentences_df.loc[index, 'sharing_type'] = 'protective'\n","#     elif is_concerning and not is_protective: sharing_senten