n the defined lists.\n","\n","### Insights or Next Steps\n","\n","*   The initial categorization provides a foundational understanding of each app's privacy posture across different dimensions. Further analysis should now focus on aggregating these per-app breakdowns to identify overall trends and outliers, especially concerning 'Data Sharing/Third Parties'.\n","*   The keyword-based classification for 'protective' vs. 'concerning' data sharing language serves as a good initial filter. For a more nuanced understanding, the 'neutral' sentences (189 sentences) within the 'Data Sharing/Third Parties' category could be manually reviewed or subjected to more advanced natural language processing (NLP) techniques to identify latent protective or concerning aspects not caught by simple keyword matching.\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"id":"010cefa1","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1763066199072,"user_tz":360,"elapsed":342,"user":{"displayName":"Alexis Prieto","userId":"17070250717485939340"}},"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":490},"outputId":"624c34f4-6d2f-442c-e925-2371e0cb5109"},"source":["import pandas as pd\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","import seaborn as sns\n","\n","# Load the app summary dataframe\n","app_summary_df = pd.read_csv('privacy_risk_by_app_updated.csv')\n","\n","# Sort by privacy risk percentage for better visualization\n","app_summary_df = app_summary_df.sort_values('privacy_risk_percentage', ascending=False)\n","\n","plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n","sns.barplot(\n","    x='app',\n","    y='privacy_risk_percentage',\n","    data=app_summary_df,\n","    palette='viridis'\n",")\n","plt.title('Privacy Risk Ranking by App (Percentage of Risky Sentences)')\n","plt.xlabel('App Name')\n","plt.ylabel('Privacy Risk Percentage (%)')\n","plt.ylim(0, 100) # Ensure y-axis goes from 0 to 100\n","plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right') # Rotate x-axis labels for readability\n","\n","# Add exact percentage values on top of the ba