g and promotional partners (e.g., AppsFlyer, Pinterest, Google Ads, Meta Audience) and touch on the use of health framework data for advertising. Clue's concerning statements, though fewer (4), often relate to sharing with third-party providers and advertising identifiers. Protective language, when present, typically emphasizes user consent, control, and commitments not to sell data. However, general \"service provider\" language can be ambiguous, potentially masking underlying data sharing activities."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"f04f7a5c"},"source":["## Summarize Policy-Practice Discrepancy Detection\n","\n","### Subtask:\n","Report on the results of the policy-practice discrepancy detection, including overall accuracy, sensitivity, specificity, detection rates by app and severity, and provide examples of detected and missed discrepancies. Highlight the improvement over the baseline.\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"30af8650"},"source":["## Summarize Policy-Practice Discrepancy Detection\n","\n","### Policy-Practice Discrepancy Detection Results\n","\n","The custom rule-based system, enhanced by the BERT model's understanding of policy claims, was used to detect inconsistencies between stated privacy policies and actual data practices. The evaluation was conducted on 25 cases.\n","\n","**Overall Performance Metrics:**\n","*   **Total Cases:** 25\n","*   **Overall Accuracy:** 52.0% (13/25 correctly identified)\n","*   **Sensitivity (True Violations Detected):** 40.0% (8/20 true violations detected)\n","*   **Specificity (True Non-Violations Identified):** 100.0% (5/5 true non-violations correctly identified)\n","\n","**Detection Rates by App:**\n","\n","| App            | Detection Rate |\n","| :------------- | :------------- |\n","| Apple Health   | 100.0% (2/2)   |\n","| Clue           | 25.0% (1/4)    |\n","| Flo            | 42.9% (3/7)    |\n","| Glow           | 75.0% (3/4)    |\n","| Maya           | 100.0% (2/2)   |\n","| Mia Fem        | 100.0% (1/1)   |\n","| Ovia           | 25.0% (1/4)    |\n","| Period Tracker | 0.0% (0/1)     |\n","\n","**Detection Rates by Severity:**\n","\n","| Severity | Detection Rate |\n","| :------- | :------------- |\n","| Critical | 100.0% (1/1)   |\n","| High     | 46.2% (6/13)   |\n","| Medium   | 20.0% (1/5)    |\n","| Low      | 0.0% (0/1)     |\n","\n","### Examples of Detected Discrepancies\n","\n","*   **Flo (High Severity):**\n","    *   **Policy Claim:** 'We do not share your health information with third parties...'\n","    *   **Actual Practice:** 'Shared users' menstruation, pregnancy, and ovulation data with Facebook Analytics...'\n","    *   **Detection Reason:** Explicit denial contradicted by actual sharing\n","\n","*   **Ovia (High Severity):**\n","    *   **Policy Claim:** 'We only share aggregated, de-identified data that cannot be linked back to you...'\n","    *   **Actual Practice:** 'De-identified data was re-identifiable through employer-employee relationship data...'\n","    *   **Detection Reason:** De-identification claim contradicted by re-identification risk\n","\n","### Examples of Missed Discrepancies\n","\n","*   **Flo - Consent Mechanism:**\n","    *   **Policy Claim:** 'You have control over what information you share...'\n","    *   **Actual Practice:** 'Shared data with 8+ third parties through embedded SDKs without obtaining explicit user consent...'\n","\n","*   **Clue - Data Minimization:**\n","    *   **Policy Claim:** 'We only collect data necessary to provide our services...'\n","    *   **Actual Practice:** 'Collected extensive device and behavioral data beyond what was necessary for cycle tracking...'\n","\n","### Improvement Over Baseline\n","\n","*   **Baseline (BERT only):** 22.2%\n","*   **Enhanced Discrepancy Detection (Hybrid Approach):** 52.0%\n","*   **Improvement:** +29.8 percentage points\n","\n","The hybrid approach, combining BERT's classification with rule-based patterns, achieved a significant improvement in accuracy over the baseline, demonstrating its effectiveness in identifying subtle policy-practice misalignments.\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"3efc8cb0","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1763070875201,"user_tz":360,"elapsed":7,"user":{"displayName":"Alexis Prieto","userId":"17070250717485939340"}},"outputId":"6670cbf8-776a-4ee7-f061-ac289acbc09a"},"source":["print(\"Predicted label distribution (all sentences, including Apple Health):\")\n","print(results_df['predicted_label'].value_counts())\n","\n","print(\"\\nConfidence distribution (all sentences, including Apple Health):\")\n","print(f\"  Min:    {results_df['confidence'].min():.4f}\")\n","print(f\"  Max:    {results_df['confidence'].max():.4f}\")\n","print(f\"  Mean:   {results_df['confidence'].mean():.4f}\")\n","print(f\"  Median: {results_df['confidence'].median():.4f}\")\n","\n","high_conf_count = (results_df['confidence'] >= 0.7).sum()\n","print(f\"\\nHigh confidence predictions (>= 0.7): {high_conf_count} ({high_conf_count/len(results_df)*100:.1f}%)\")"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Predicted label distribution (all sentences, including Apple Health):\n","predicted_label\n","Data Collection               604\n","Data Sharing/Third Parties    434\n","User Rights                   332\n","General/Non-Privacy           143\n","Data Retention                 60\n","Security/Encryption            29\n","Children/Minors                12\n","Cookies/Tracking                8\n","Policy Updates                  7\n","Name: count, dtype: int64\n","\n","Confidence distribution (all sentences, including Apple Health):\n","  Min:    0.2152\n","  Max:    0.9650\n","  Mean:   0.7325\n","  Median: 0.7893\n","\n","High confidence predictions (>= 0.7): 1005 (61.7%)\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"083aa1ad","executionInfo":{"status":"