n","metadata":{"id":"677d8fd7"},"source":["## Summary:\n","\n","### Data Analysis Key Findings\n","\n","*   The `apple_health_policy.txt` file was successfully loaded and incorporated into the analysis by updating its file path in the relevant code cells.\n","*   The combined dataset (`df_all`) for inference now consists of 1629 sentences from 6 unique applications, with `apple_health` contributing 113 sentences.\n","*   The BERT model performed inference on all 1629 sentences, achieving an average confidence score of 0.7325. Notably, 61.7% of all predictions had a confidence level of 0.7 or higher.\n","*   In the privacy risk analysis, Apple Health ranked highest with 85.84% (97 out of 113) of its sentences falling into privacy-concerning categories (Data Collection, Data Sharing/Third Parties, Cookies/Tracking, Data Retention).\n","*   The analysis generated updated output files including `bert_full_predictions_updated.csv`, `privacy_risk_by_app_updated.csv`, `privacy_category_distribution_updated.csv`, and a comprehensive `inference_summary_updated.txt`.\n","\n","### Insights or Next Steps\n","\n","*   The high privacy risk percentage of Apple Health (85.84%) suggests a significant portion of its policy details practices relevant to data collection, sharing, retention, or tracking. Further investigation into the specific sentences flagged could provide deeper understanding of its privacy posture.\n","*   Considering the successful integration and analysis of Apple Health data, the methodology can now be confidently applied to other privacy policies to establish a broader comparative privacy risk assessment across various applications.\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"713d97f3"},"source":["# Task\n","## Analysis of Data Sharing Language (Protective vs. Concerning)\n","\n","Further analysis of sentences categorized as 'Data Sharing/Third Parties' based on keyword matching reveals the nuanced nature of these policies.\n","\n","### Categorization of 'Data Sharing/Third Parties' sentences:\n","*   **Total sentences analyzed:** 434\n","*   **Protective:** 19 sentences (4.4%)\n","*   **Concerning:** 77 sentences (17.7%)\n","*   **Neutral:** 338 sentences (77.9%)\n","\n","This indicates that while a significant portion of data sharing language is neutral, a notable number of sentences contain concerning keywords, and only a small fraction explicitly use protective language.\n","\n","### Examples of Data Sharing Language:\n","\n","**Protective Example (Flo):**\n","  *   Sentence: \"Third-party services (including wearables): With your consent, you may also allow us to connect to third-party services, such as Apple HealthKit and Google Health Connect.\"\n","  *   App: flo\n","  *   Predicted Label: Data Sharing/Third Parties\n","  *   Confidence: 0.9552\n","\n","**Concerning Example (Ovia):**\n","  *   Sentence: \"Categories of Recipients Examples of Recipients We Share With Service Providers and Contractors Ovia’s data is processed and stored by service providers and contractors working on Ovia’s behalf, including our cloud services provider Amazon Web Services, Helpshift (support services platform), Salesforce.com (coaching platform), Alchemer (survey platform) and Zoom Video Communications (coaching communications).\"\n","  *   App: ovia\n","  *   Predicted Label: Data Sharing/Third Parties\n","  *   Confidence: 0.9450\n","\n","### Confidence Scores for 'Concerning' Data Sharing Sentences (Flo, Clue, Ovia):\n","\n","| App    | Num Concerning Sentences | Min Confidence | Max Confidence | Mean Confidence | Median Confidence |\n","| :----- | :----------------------- | :------------- | :------------- | :-------------- | :---------------- |\n","| Flo    | 15                       | 0.4415         | 0.9575         | 0.8034          | 0.8895            |\n","| Clue   | 4                        | 0.3396         | 0.9528         | 0.5935          | 0.5407            |\n","| Ovia   | 34                       | 0.4788         | 0.9628         | 0.9015          | 0.9515            |\n","\n","### Key Observations about Data Sharing Practices:\n","Ovia has the highest number of concerning data sharing sentences (34), often explicitly mentioning advertising IDs, networks, and potential compensation for data, pointing to a higher risk profile related to data monetization. The model's confidence for these classifications is generally high. Flo's concerning statements frequently involve sharing with marketing and promotional partners (e.g., AppsFlyer, Pinterest, Google Ads, Meta Audience) and touch on the use of health framework data for advertising. Clue's concerning statements, though fewer (4), often relate to sharing with third-party providers and advertising identifiers. Protective language, when present, typically emphasizes user consent, control, and commitments not to sell data. However, general \"service provider\" language can be ambiguous, potentially masking underlying data sharing activities."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"bcbd49cb"},"source":["## Analyze Data Sharing Language (Protective vs. Concerning)\n","\n","### Subtask:\n","Summarize the findings from the data sharing language analysis, including the total counts and percentages of sentences categorized as 'protective,' 'concerning,' and 'neutral' across all apps. Provide examples of protective and concerning sentences, and detail the confidence scores (min, max, mean, median) for concerning sentences for Flo, Clue, and Ovia. Include the key observations about data sharing practices for these apps.\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"7a5ba082"},"source":["## Summary:\n","\n","### Q&A\n","\n","1.  **What is the summary of findings from the data sharing language analysis across all apps?**\n","    Out of 434 analyzed sentences related to data sharing, 19 (4.4%) were categorized as protective, 77 (17.7%) as concerning, and 338 (77.9%) as neutral.\n","2.  **Can you provide examples of protective and concerning sentences?**\n","    A protective example from Flo states: \"Third-party services (including wearables): With your consent, you may also allow us to connect to third-party services, such as Apple HealthKit and Google Health Connect.\" A concerning example from Ovia lists service providers and contractors like \"Amazon Web Services, Helpshift (support services platform), Salesforce.com (coaching platform), Alchemer (survey platform) and Zoom Video Communications (coaching communications)\" with whom Ovia's data is shared.\n","3.  **What are the confidence scores for concerning sentences for Flo, Clue, and Ovia?**\n","    *   **Flo (15 concerning sentences):** Min Confidence: 0.4415, Max Confidence: 0.9575, Mean Confidence: 0.8034, Median Confidence: 0.8895.\n","    *   **Clue (4 concerning sentences):** Min Confidence: 0.3396, Max Confidence: 0.9528, Mean Confidence: 0.5935, Median Confidence: 0.5407.\n","    *   **Ovia (34 concerning sentences):** Min Confidence: 0.4788, Max Confidence: 0.9628, Mean Confidence: 0.9015, Median Confidence: 0.9515.\n","4.  **What are the key observations about data sharing practices for these apps?**\n","    Ovia has the highest number of concerning data sharing sentences (34), frequently mentioning advertising IDs, networks, and potential data monetization, indicating a higher risk. Flo's concerning statements often involve sharing with marketing and promotional partners (e.g., AppsFlyer, Pinterest, Google Ads, Meta Audience) and using health framework data for advertising. Clue, despite having fewer concerning statements (4), still raises issues related to sharing with third-party providers and advertising identifiers. Protective language typically emphasizes user consent and control, but general \"service provider\" phrasing can be ambiguous.\n","\n","### Data Analysis Key Findings\n","\n","*   A minority of data sharing sentences (17.7%) were found to be concerning, while an even smaller fraction (4.4%) used protective language across all analyzed apps.\n","*   Ovia exhibited the highest number of concerning data sharing sentences, with 34 instances, often detailing explicit sharing for advertising and potential compensation for data.\n","*   Flo's 15 concerning sentences primarily related to sharing user data with various marketing and promotional partners, including major advertising platforms.\n","*   The confidence scores for identifying concerning sentences were generally high, especially for Ovia (mean confidence of 0.9015 and median of 0.9515), suggesting robust classification.\n","*   Protective language typically highlighted user consent and control, or commitments not to sell data, but was far less prevalent than concerning or neutral statements.\n","\n","### Insights or Next Steps\n","\n","*   Further investigation is needed into the specific implications of \"service provider\" language, as its ambiguity may obscure actual data sharing practices and risks.\n","*   Apps should be encouraged to adopt clearer and more explicit protective language to enhance user trust and transparency, particularly given the low prevalence of such statements.\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"4adff7bc"},"source":["# Task\n","Read and display the content of the `inference_summary_updated.txt` file."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"de8d9fe3"},"source":["## Review the inference_summary_updated.txt file\n","\n","### Subtask:\n","Re-read and display the content of the `inference_summary_updated.txt` file to reflect the latest analysis that includes Apple Health.\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"9db03649"},"source":["**Reasoning**:\n","The subtask requires reading and displaying the content of the `inference_summary_updated.txt` file. This Python code will open the file, read its content, and then print it to the console.\n","\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"0128b6e9","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1764130565836,"user_tz":360,"elapsed":69569,"user":{"displayName":"Alexis Prieto","userId":"17070250717485939340"}},"outputId":"03bc6d18-ee09-42b5-f7dd-fef2be0fc62b"},"source":["import pandas as pd\n","import numpy as np\n","import torch\n","from torch.utils.data import DataLoader, Dataset\n","from transformers import BertForSequenceClassification, BertTokenizer\n","import warnings\n","import re\n","import os\n","warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n","\n","print(\"=\"*70)\n","print(\"RE-INITIALIZING DATA AND RE-RUNNING FULL INFERENCE\")\n","print(\"=\"*70)\n","\n","# Explicitly define paths to ensure they are in scope\n","base_path = '/content/drive/MyDrive/femtech-bert-project'\n","data_path = f'{base_path}/data'\n","models_path = f'{base_path}/models'\n","\n","# --- Step 1: Re-create df_all --- #\n","\n","# Load original all_sentences.csv\n","df_all_original = pd.read_csv(f'{data_path}/all_sentences.csv')\n","\n","# Re-load df_apple_health\n","# This assumes 'apple_health_policy.txt' was successfully uploaded and is accessible.\n","# For robustness, we re-tokenize it here if needed, or assume df_apple_health is in scope.\n","\n","# Check if df_apple_health exists in current session, if not, try to recreate from file\n","if 'df_apple_health' not in locals() and 'df_apple_health' not in globals():\n","    print(\"\\nRecreating df_apple_health from 'apple_health_policy.txt'...\")\n","    try:\n","        import nltk\n","        from nltk.tokenize import sent_tokenize\n","        try:\n","            nltk.data.find('tokenizers/punkt')\n","        except LookupError:\n","            nltk.download('punkt')\n","        try:\n","            nltk.data.find('tokenizers/punkt_tab')\n","        except LookupError:\n","            nltk.download('punkt_tab')\n","\n","        apple_health_file_path = f'{data_path}/privacy_policies/apple_health_policy.txt'\n","        with open(apple_health_file_path, 'r') as f:\n","            text_content_apple_health = f.read()\n","        sentences_apple_health = sent_tokenize(text_content_apple_health)\n","        df_apple_health = pd.DataFrame({\n","            'sentence': sentences_apple_health,\n","            'app': 'apple_health'\n","        })\n","        print(f\"  Successfully recreated {len(df_apple_health)} sentences for Apple Health.\")\n","    except FileNotFoundError:\n","        print(\"  Warning: 'apple_health_policy.txt' not found. Apple Health data will not be included.\")\n","        df_apple_health = pd.DataFrame(columns=['sentence', 'app']) # Create empty df\n","    except Exception as e:\n","        print(f\"  Error recreating df_apple_health: {e}. Apple Health data will not be included.\")\n","        df_apple_health = pd.DataFrame(columns=['sentence', 'app'])\n","\n","# Combine the dataframes to form the complete df_all for this execution\n","df_all = pd.concat([df_all_original, df_apple_health], ignore_index=True)\n","\n","print(f\"\\nCombined df_all created with {len(df_all)} sentences.\")\n","print(f\"Apps in df_all: {df_all['app'].unique().tolist()}\")\n","\n","# --- Start Full Inference Logic (from 0a62b357) --- #\n","\n","print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*70)\n","print(\"PHASE 4: FULL INFERENCE ON ALL SENTENCES (Updated with Apple Health)\")\n","print(\"=\"*70)\n","\n","# Label mapping\n","id_to_label = {\n","    0: 'Data Collection',\n","    1: 'Data Sharing/Third Parties',\n","    2: 'Data Retention',\n","    3: 'User Rights',\n","    4: 'Security/Encryption',\n","    5: 'Cookies/Tracking',\n","    6: 'Children/Minors',\n","    7: 'Policy Updates',\n","    8: 'General/Non-Privacy'\n","}\n","\n","# STEP 1: Using the combined dataset (df_all)\n","print(\"\\nSTEP 1: Using the combined dataset (df_all)\")\n","print(\"-\" * 70)\n","\n","print(f\"Loaded {len(df_all)} sentences\")\n","print(f\"Apps: {df_all['app'].unique().tolist()}\")\n","print(f\"App distribution:\")\n","print(df_all['app'].value_counts())\n","\n","# STEP 2: Load trained model\n","print(\"\\nSTEP 2: Loading trained BERT model\")\n","print(\"-\" * 70)\n","\n","device = torch.device('cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu')\n","print(f\"Using device: {device}\")\n","\n","# Load model and tokenizer from the models_path\n","model_load_path = f'{models_path}/bert_privacy_classifier'\n","model = BertForSequenceClassification.from_pretrained(model_load_path)\n","tokenizer = BertTokenizer.from_pretrained(model_load_path)\n","model.to(device)\n","model.eval()\n","\n","print(\"Model loaded successfully\")\n","\n","# STEP 3: Create inference dataset\n","print(\"\\nSTEP 3: Preparing for inference\")\n","print(\"-\" * 70)\n","\n","class InferenceDataset(Dataset):\n","    def __init__(self, texts, tokenizer, max_length=256):\n","        self.encodings = tokenizer(\n","            texts.tolist(), # Convert numpy array to list\n","            truncation=True,\n","            padding=True,\n","            max_length=max_length,\n","            return_tensors='pt'\n","        )\n","\n","    def __len__(self):\n","        return len(self.encodings['input_ids'])\n","\n","    def __getitem__(self, idx):\n","        return {\n","            'input_ids': self.encodings['input_ids'][idx],\n","            'attention_mask': self.encodings['attention_mask'][idx]\n","        }\n","\n","inference_dataset = InferenceDataset(df_all['sentence'].values, tokenizer)\n","inference_loader = DataLoader(inference_dataset, batch_size=16, shuffle=False)\n","\n","print(f\"Inference dataset: {len(inference_dataset)} sentences\")\n","print(f\"Batch size: 16\")\n","\n","# STEP 4: Run inference\n","print(\"\\nSTEP 4: Running inference\")\n","print(\"-\" * 70)\n","\n","all_preds = []\n","all_probs = []\n","all_confidences = []\n","\n","with torch.no_grad():\n","    for batch_idx, batch in enumerate(inference_loader):\n","        if (batch_idx + 1) % 20 == 0:\n","            print(f\"  Processed: {min((batch_idx + 1) * 16, len(inference_dataset))}/{len(inference_dataset)}\")\n","\n","        input_ids = batch['input_ids'].to(device)\n","        attention_mask = batch['attention_mask'].to(device)\n","\n","        outputs = model(input_ids=input_ids, attention_mask=attention_mask)\n","        logits = outputs.logits\n","        probs = torch.softmax(logits, dim=1)\n","        preds = torch.argmax(logits, dim=1)\n","        confidences = torch.max(probs, dim=1)[0]\n","\n","        all_preds.extend(preds.cpu().numpy())\n","        all_probs.extend(probs.cpu().numpy())\n","        all_confidences.extend(confidences.cpu().numpy())\n","\n","print(f\"Inference complete: {len(all_preds)} predictions\")\n","\n","# STEP 5: Create results dataframe\n","print(\"\\nSTEP 5: Creating results\")\n","print(\"-\" * 70)\n","\n","results_df = df_all.copy()\n","results_df['predicted_label'] = [id_to_label[p] for p in all_preds]\n","results_df['predicted_label_code'] = np.array(all_preds) + 1\n","results_df['confidence'] = all_confidences\n","\n","# Add top-3 predictions\n","for i in range(3):\n","    col_name = f'prediction_{i+1}_label'\n","    conf_name = f'prediction_{i+1}_confidence'\n","\n","    top_k_indices = np.argsort(-np.array(all_probs), axis=1)[:, i]\n","    results_df[col_name] = [id_to_label[idx] for idx in top_k_indices]\n","    results_df[conf_name] = [all_probs[j][top_k_indices[j]] for j in range(len(top_k_indices))]\n","\n","print(f\"Results dataframe created: {len(results_df)} rows\")\n","print(f\"Columns: {results_df.columns.tolist()}\")\n","\n","# STEP 6: Generate statistics\n","print(\"\\nSTEP 6: Generating statistics\")\n","print(\"-\" * 70)\n","\n","print(\"\\nPredicted label distribution (all sentences):\")\n","print(results_df['predicted_label'].value_counts())\n","\n","print(\"\\nConfidence distribution:\")\n","print(f\"  Min:    {results_df['confidence'].min():.4f}\")\n","print(f\"  Max:    {results_df['confidence'].max():.4f}\")\n","print(f\"  Mean:   {results_df['confidence'].mean():.4f}\")\n","print(f\"  Median: {results_df['confidence'].median():.4f}\")\n","\n","high_conf_count = (results_df['confidence'] >= 0.7).sum()\n","print(f\"\\nHigh confidence predictions (>= 0.7): {high_conf_count} ({high_conf_count/len(results_df)*100:.1f}%)\")\n","\n","# STEP 7: Privacy risk analysis by app\n","print(\"\\nSTEP 7: Privacy risk analysis by app\")\n","print(\"-\" * 70)\n","\n","privacy_risk_categories = [\n","    'Data Collection',\n","    'Data Sharing/Third Parties',\n","    'Cookies/Tracking',\n","    'Data Retention'\n","]\n","\n","app_analysis = []\n","\n","for app in sorted(results_df['app'].unique()):\n","    app_data = results_df[results_df['app'] == app]\n","\n","    total_sentences = len(app_data)\n","\n","    privacy_risk_count = app_data[app_data['predicted_label'].isin(privacy_risk_categories)].shape[0]\n","    privacy_risk_pct = privacy_risk_count / total_sentences * 100\n","\n","    avg_confidence = app_data['confidence'].mean()\n","\n","    label_dist = app_data['predicted_label'].value_counts()\n","\n","    app_analysis.append({\n","        'app': app,\n","        'total_sentences': total_sentences,\n","        'privacy_risk_sentences': privacy_risk_count,\n","        'privacy_risk_percentage': privacy_risk_pct,\n","        'avg_confidence': avg_confidence,\n","        'data_collection': label_dist.get('Data Collection', 0),\n","        'data_sharing': label_dist.get('Data Sharing/Third Parties', 0),\n","        'cookies_tracking': label_dist.get('Cookies/Tracking', 0),\n","        'data_retention': label_dist.get('Data Retention', 0),\n","        'user_rights': label_dist.get('User Rights', 0),\n","    })\n","\n","app_summary_df = pd.DataFrame(app_analysis)\n","app_summary_df = app_summary_df.sort_values('privacy_risk_percentage', ascending=False)\n","\n","print(\"\\nApp Privacy Risk Ranking:\")\n","print(app_summary_df[['app', 'total_sentences', 'privacy_risk_sentences', 'privacy_risk_percentage', 'avg_confidence']].to_string(index=False))\n","\n","# STEP 8: Save results\n","print(\"\\nSTEP 8: Saving results\")\n","print(\"-\" * 70)\n","\n","results_df.to_csv('bert_full_predictions_updated.csv', index=False)\n","print(\"Saved: bert_full_predictions_updated.csv\")\n","\n","app_summary_df.to_csv('privacy_risk_by_app_updated.csv', index=False)\n","print(\"Saved: privacy_risk_by_app_updated.csv\")\n","\n","# Category distribution\n","category_dist = results_df['predicted_label'].value_counts().to_frame('count')\n","category_dist['percentage'] = (category_dist['count'] / len(results_df) * 100).round(2)\n","category_dist.to_csv('privacy_category_distribution_updated.csv')\n","print(\"Saved: privacy_category_distribution_updated.csv\")\n","\n","# STEP 9: Generate summary report\n","print(\"\\nSTEP 9: Generating summary report\")\n","print(\"-\" * 70)\n","\n","summary_text = f\"\"\"\n","BERT FULL INFERENCE SUMMARY (Updated with Apple Health)\n","{'='*70}\n","\n","Dataset Overview:\n","  Total sentences analyzed: {len(results_df):,}\n","  Unique apps: {results_df['app'].nunique()}\n","  Average confidence: {results_df['confidence'].mean():.4f}\n","\n","Privacy Category Distribution:\n","\"\"\"\n","\n","for label, count in results_df['predicted_label'].value_counts().items():\n","    pct = count / len(results_df) * 100\n","    summary_text += f\"  {label:30s}: {count:4d} ({pct:5.1f}%)\\n\"\n","\n","summary_text += f\"\"\"\n","\n","Privacy Risk Assessment:\n","  Privacy-concerning categories: Data Collection, Data Sharing/Third Parties,\n","                                  Cookies/Tracking, Data Retention\n","\n","  Apps by privacy risk (% of sentences in risk categories):\n","\"\"\"\n","\n","for idx, row in app_summary_df.head(7).iterrows():\n","    summary_text += f\"  {row['app']:20s}: {row['privacy_risk_percentage']:5.1f}% ({row['privacy_risk_sentences']}/{row['total_sentences']} sentences)\\n\"\n","\n","summary_text += f\"\"\"\n","\n","Confidence Analysis:\n","  High confidence (>= 0.7): {high_conf_count:4d} ({high_conf_count/len(results_df)*100:5.1f}%)\n","  Min confidence: {results_df['confidence'].min():.4f}\n","  Max confidence: {results_df['confidence'].max():.4f}\n","\n","Key Findings:\n","  1. Most common privacy categories: {results_df['predicted_label'].value_counts().index[0]}, {results_df['predicted_label'].value_counts().index[1]}\n","  2. Highest privacy risk app: {app_summary_df.iloc[0]['app']} ({app_summary_df.iloc[0]['privacy_risk_percentage']:.1f}%)\n","  3. Model confidence: Average {results_df['confidence'].mean():.1%}\n","\n","Files Generated:\n","  - bert_full_predictions_updated.csv: All sentences with predictions\n","  - privacy_risk_by_app_updated.csv: Summary statistics per app\n","  - privacy_category_distribution_updated.csv: Category breakdown\n","  - inference_summary_updated.txt: Summary report\n","\"\"\"\n","\n","with open('inference_summary_updated.txt', 'w') as f:\n","    f.write(summary_text)\n","\n","print(summary_text)\n","print(\"\\nSaved: inference_summary_updated.txt\")\n","\n","print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*70)\n","print(\"PHASE 4 COMPLETE (Updated)\")\n","print(\"=\"*70)\n","print(\"\\nFiles ready for download:\")\n","print(\"  1. bert_full_predictions_updated.csv - All predictions\")\n","print(\"  2. privacy_risk_by_app_updated.csv - Risk analysis by app\")\n","print(\"  3. privacy_category_distribution_updated.csv - Category breakdown\")\n","print(\"  4. inference_summary_updated.txt - Summary report\")\n"],"execution_count":1,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["======================================================================\n","RE-INITIALIZING DATA AND RE-RUNNING FULL INFERENCE\n","======================================================================\n","\n","Recreating df_apple_health from 'apple_health_policy.txt'...\n"]},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stderr","text":["[nltk_data] Downloading package punkt to /root/nltk_data...\n","[nltk_data]   Unzipping tokenizers/punkt.zip.\n","[nltk_data] Downloading package punkt_tab to /root/nltk_data...\n","[nltk_data]   Unzipping tokenizer